description: head and shoulder portrait of man with long culy wig and black coat with white stock at neck; 3/4 view of subject looking left; rust geometric border printed around sheet near edge
inscription:
Title and Inscriptions

on sheet below image in black:[LUDULPH BACKHUYSEN/ Ships, Sea-pieces/ Born 1631-Died 1709]; on sheet above border upper right in rust: [I P 63]; below image in pencil lower right: [1-63]; verso upperright corner in pencil: [86]
title: Portrait of Ludulph Backhuysen
